  <prompt>
    Author / extend the Phase 4 integration test suite covering the 4 spec.md Success Criteria T-002, T-004, T-005, T-009. These tests exercise the end-to-end 6-tier memory subsystem (T2 session memory + upload pipeline; T3 matter memory + promotion; T5 retrieval over chat-domain indexes; T6 audit). **Cross-wave dep on 064** (frontend build) — the test suite exercises the frontend `memory` channel subscriber path; main session MUST verify 064 ✅ before dispatching this task.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform test engineer with end-to-end integration test expertise (BFF + frontend memory event subscribers + Azure AI Search + Cosmos).</role>

  <goal>
    Integration test suite passes for T-002, T-004, T-005, T-009. Tests assert: (T-002) session-file recall returns citations on requireCitations=true; (T-004) promote_to_matter_memory drives full Cosmos pending-record → `memory.promotion_pending` → ContextPane subscriber → approve → `MatterMemoryService.AppendFactAsync` → `memory.fact_promoted` chain; (T-005) Tier 5 retrieval handlers query ONLY chat-domain indexes; (T-009) FR-25 audit-only `sprk_aichatmessage` write succeeds without violating ADR-015 tier-1 fields.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec.md Success Criteria. T-002 covers `recall_session_file` citation enforcement (FR-29 + FR-31). T-004 covers FR-32 memory-promotion full chain (Cosmos doc-type `matter-memory-promotion` + new `memory` PaneEventBus channel from ADR-030 v2 amendment + ContextPane subscriber from task 098). T-005 covers FR-36 chat-domain index isolation per architecture §5.2.1 (zero `spaarke-insights-index` reads). T-009 covers FR-25 `sprk_aichatmessage` write-only audit. Cross-wave dep on 064: T-004 chain reaches the frontend subscriber; frontend build must compile cleanly per task 064 before integration tests are meaningful.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Memory/</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/context/</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/types/PaneEventTypes.ts</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec T-002">Citation enforcement: `recall_session_file` with `requireCitations: true` returns citations alongside content; LLM must cite per persona instruction.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec T-004">Promotion full chain: Cosmos pending-record → `memory.promotion_pending` → ContextPane subscriber → approve → `MatterMemoryService.AppendFactAsync` → `memory.promotion_resolved` + `memory.fact_promoted` + `context.decision_made` audit emission.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec T-005">Tier 5 wraps chat-domain indexes only; `grep "spaarke-insights-index"` returns zero hits in chat-memory paths.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec T-009">FR-25: `sprk_aichatmessage` write-only audit; integration test confirms writes succeed; zero reads remain.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Tier-1 logging in test assertions: tests assert NO query text, file content, recall results, or memory facts surface in App Insights / log output paths.</constraint>
    <constraint source="cross-wave">Task 064 (frontend build) must be ✅ before dispatching this task; main session verifies before parallel-wave fan-out.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
