  <steps>
    <step order="1">Verify cross-wave prereqs in TASK-INDEX: task 064 (frontend build) = ✅ AND task 102 (write-only verification) = ✅. If either is not ✅, STOP and report.</step>
    <step order="2">Read spec.md Success Criteria T-002, T-004, T-005, T-009 in full. Note expected acceptance signals per test.</step>
    <step order="3">For T-002 (citation enforcement): author/extend `RecallSessionFileHandlerIntegrationTests` — upload a test PDF; invoke `recall_session_file(mode='section', purpose='quote', requireCitations=true)`; assert response includes `citations[]` with page + paragraph + text; assert truncation_reason field set correctly.</step>
    <step order="4">For T-004 (promotion full chain): author end-to-end test — POST `promote_to_matter_memory` via handler → assert Cosmos `memory` container has `matter-memory-promotion_{guid}` doc; assert `memory.promotion_pending` event dispatched (verify via test event-bus harness); simulate POST `/api/memory/promotions/{id}/approve` → assert `MatterMemoryService.AppendFactAsync` called with correct fact; assert `memory.promotion_resolved { decision: 'approved' }` + `memory.fact_promoted { factId, matterId }` events dispatched; assert `context.decision_made` audit event emitted to Cosmos `audit`.</step>
    <step order="5">For T-005 (Tier 5 chat-domain isolation): author static-grep test (or runtime assertion harness) that confirms recall handler classes target only `spaarke-session-files` / `spaarke-files-index` / `spaarke-rag-references`; assert constructor of any chat-memory retrieval handler throws when passed an `spaarke-insights-index` configuration.</step>
    <step order="6">For T-009 (FR-25 audit write): author integration test that triggers a chat session save → assert `sprk_aichatmessage` write succeeds (via Dataverse Web API check); assert zero read paths invoked on the entity during normal chat flow; assert audit consumers read from Cosmos `audit` container instead.</step>
    <step order="7">Run the new tests via `dotnet test tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/`. All 4 must pass.</step>
    <step order="8">Spot-check frontend memory subscriber behavior via the `SpaarkeAi` test harness (Vitest or equivalent) — verify `usePaneEvent('memory', ...)` receives the dispatched events during the T-004 flow.</step>
    <step order="9">Document test outputs at `notes/handoffs/103-phase4-integration-test-report.md`.</step>
    <step order="10">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 103 → ✅; current-task.md → ready for 104.</step>
  </steps>

